<div class = "aboutme">
<h3> About the Owner </h3>
<p>Danielle is a sophomore at Syracuse University majoring in Information Technology with a minor in Marketing. She has decided to dedicate her remaining years to help decrease the poverty rate in Syracuse. She wants to do this by educating the youth by introducing them to STEM related fields, as well is utilzing resources on her university to give them basic life essentials. Before coming to campus, Danielle started a Women's Empowerment Club at her highschool. This organization worked to educate women in their distrct, as well as iniate a campaign to give out free feminine products throughout their highschool. This was the start of Danielle's advocacy work. She then became the Philanthropy Chair for her professional fraternity Alpha Kappa Psi, where she worked to encourage the brotherhood to participate in more community service projects across the community. Before she leaves campus, she aspires to create her impact on Syracuse through Syracuse Uprise.Learn more about Danielle<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/danielle-nimako/"> here. </a> <p>
</div>
